2. In these Directions, unless the context otherwise requires- Interpretation
"basic school" means a school that consists of primary and secondary school
classes;
"Commission" means the Teaching Service Commission established by section
seven of the Act;
"headmaster (basic)" means a headmaster of a grade I, II, III or IV basic school
and, " deputy headmaster" shall be construed accordingly;
"headmaster (primary)" means a headmaster of a grade I, II, III or IV primary
school and, "deputy headmaster" shall be construed accordingly;
"headmaster (secondary)" means a headmaster of a grade I, II, III or IV secondary
school and "deputy headmaster" shall be construed accordingly;
